# Gushwork Assessment

This project is a responsive web page developed as part of the **Gushwork Frontend Assessment**.  
The page is implemented using **Vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript only**, without using any frameworks or external libraries.

The goal of the project is to create a **pixel-accurate, responsive, and interactive webpage** based on the design provided in the Figma file.

---

## Design Reference
Figma Design:  
https://www.figma.com/design/DOv07H7C2tA5UrVLhmfwfW/Gushwork-Assignment

The layout, styling, spacing, and interactive elements were implemented following the design specifications in the Figma file.

---

## Key Features

### Responsive Design
The webpage is fully responsive and adapts to different screen sizes including:
- Desktop
- Tablet
- Mobile devices

CSS media queries and flexible layouts are used to ensure proper alignment and spacing across devices.

### Sticky Header with Scroll Behavior
The header includes dynamic scroll functionality implemented using JavaScript.

- Header stays fixed at the top of the page
- Appears when the user scrolls down
- Hides when scrolling back up
- Smooth transition effects for better user experience

### Smooth Scrolling Navigation
Navigation links smoothly scroll to different sections of the webpage using JavaScript.

### Dark Mode Toggle
A dark mode feature is implemented that allows users to switch between **light and dark themes** dynamically.

### Education Journey Slider
A slider component is implemented to display educational milestones.  
Users can navigate between slides using previous and next buttons.

### Image Gallery with Lightbox
The gallery section allows users to click on images to open a **lightbox preview**, providing a larger view of the selected image.

### Hover Effects and Animations
Various hover effects and animations are implemented using CSS transitions and keyframes to enhance user interaction.

---

## Technologies Used

- **HTML5** – Semantic page structure
- **CSS3** – Layout, animations, responsive design using Flexbox and Grid
- **JavaScript (Vanilla JS)** – Interactive components such as:
  - Sticky header behavior
  - Slider functionality
  - Dark mode toggle
  - Image lightbox

---

## Project Files

- **index.html** – Main webpage structure
- **style.css** – Styling, layout, animations, and responsive design
- **script.js** – JavaScript functionality and interactions
- Images, icons, and media assets used for the design

